age as if the phone was blocked. I didn't even bother calling to have it unblocked/fixed. I would probably have to call twice, get upset, etc. so I left it the way it is as I really don't feel like interacting with the staff.The good side? the room has impressive views and nice designed furniture. Bathtub by Philip Starck, all very nice indeed, specially if you're design oriented and really cares about this stuff, as we do. But a good hotel, those who stay on for long, is not only made by good views and design. It needs to excel in service. The next &quot;hip-place-to-be&quot; hotel is just around the corner and If I want to survive in the New York city battlefield, I would improve that aspect of my business.Def not staying again. Not worth the 600USD/night rate.	
