Jun 23 2009 	Misses the mark	The positive: The location of the hotel is fantastic and the views cannot be beat, especially from the shower/bath. Being right over the Highline is amazing too. Room was very clean, quiet and comfortable for the most part.The negative: The build quality of this hotel is not great--i think they either built too quickly or cut corners. The door didn't close properly ever b/c it seemed frame was warped--i had to slam it shut and literally kick it open several times. The hotel is brand new, this shouldn't happen. The cable went out multiple times in two days. The check out from TV didn't work when i left. When you are on the Highline and look up at the hotel, you'll see how the cement frame from floor to floor on outside has shifted in all different directions--it is not a straight line--just take a look when you are there and you'll see. The room is a little cold and uninviting. I get what they were going for, mid-century/Danish, but it somehow misses the mark and feels more like the inside of an RV with strange bolsters and railing around the room. There is a misplaced peice of furniture that is the bar that sits in the hallway; it looks like it was an afterthought and left over from a previous owner, waisting precious space. The staff, though extremely polite and friendly, are just not up to hotel staff at other established hotels--it feels like college kids are running the hotel. It could be that the property is still green and will work the kinks out, but right now, it just not there. Finally, the lobby, though trying to be cool is really unimpressive in person and too small in scale. Would I stay here again, probably not--there are better hotels near by that have a better vibe and energy than this place. Was it a bad stay, not by any means, just misses the mark.	
